Reasoning: The paper deals with the topological complexity of omega-powers, which is a topic in logic and computability theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic aspects, which suggest cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as likely sub-categories. The Dagstuhl seminar on "Topological and Game-Theoretic Aspects of Infinite Computations" also indicates a connection to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
